This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image classification and adversarial examples. It could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a framework for generating adversarial examples using deep networks. The paper also involves cryptography and security (cs.CR) as it discusses black-box attacks on classifiers. Additionally, it could be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) as it involves the use of iterative algorithms to generate adversarial examples.
